<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<sect2 xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="ch-ug-sender.GroovySender">
   <title>GroovySender</title>
   <para>
      Groovy sender can be used to implement the message sending in a Groovy script. To achieve the goal the sender uses a
      <code>groovy</code>
      installed on the system, where the PerfCake is executed.
   </para>
   <para>
      The message configured in scenario is passed to the Groovy script through standard input so it can be accessed via
      <code>System.in</code>.
   </para>
   <table frame="all">
      <title>GroovySender properties</title>
      <tgroup cols="4" align="left" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
         <colspec colname="property-name" colwidth="1*"/>
         <colspec colname="description" colwidth="1*"/>
         <colspec colname="required" colwidth="1*"/>
         <colspec colname="default-value" colwidth="1*"/>
         <thead>
            <row>
               <entry>Property name</entry>
               <entry>Description</entry>
               <entry>Required</entry>
               <entry>Default value</entry>
            </row>
         </thead>
         <tbody>
            <row>
               <entry>target</entry>
               <entry>Path to the Groovy script that is to be executed.</entry>
               <entry>Yes</entry>
               <entry>-</entry>
            </row>
         </tbody>
      </tgroup>
   </table>
   <simplesect>
      <title>Example of GroovySender configuration</title>
      <programlisting language="xml" linenumbering="numbered" startinglinenumber="1"><![CDATA[...
<sender class="GroovySender">
   <property name="target" value="/tmp/script.groovy"/>
</sender>
...]]></programlisting>
   </simplesect>
</sect2>
